p with cellulite? The answer is that they’re probably not a great cellulite solution. Massage, especially deep lymphatic drainage massage, can absolutely reduce the appearance of cellulite, at least temporarily and with regular treatment.<br><br>However, the percussive massage done with a massage gun isn’t the same as the release given with other tools. Percussive massages are excellent for releasing tense muscles and even fascia, but that doesn’t mean they can break up the connective bands or release lymph buildup, which are the fundamental reasons why some massage techniques do help with the look of cellulite.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-678b" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-ihINtW bFPXVO pf-190_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fvpsdx hSLMtg"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-191_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-678b" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-kjOQFR ctEqvM pf-192_ pf-hide"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-kjOQFR ctEqvM pf-193_"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-194_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-kjOQFR ctEqvM pf-195_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-196_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hKumaY imecqU pf-198_">Massage Gun for Cellulite: Safe or Risky?</span></h3><p class="sc-lcepkR datYlM pf-199_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Using massage guns correctly and only on soft tissue is largely safe, but there’s room for error that can lead to some serious complications.<br><br>The most major issues usually come from using a massage gun over bony areas, which is why you’ll want to be very cautious if you want to use your massage gun on your back or shoulders.<br><br> When it comes to using massage guns for cellulite, the good news is that those treatment areas are not too bony. You’ll want to be careful if you want to use it near your hips, since you can inadvertently damage the hip bone.<br><br>There is some risk to soft tissue as well, though. You can inadvertently bruise yourself if you apply too much force or use the massage gun over the same area for too long. In one case, a woman with anemia developed a serious muscle injury as a result of using a massage gun post-workout. If you have any underlying conditions, it’s important you speak to a doctor or physiotherapist before using a massage gun regularly, to make sure you do so safely.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-d629" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-ihINtW bFPXVO pf-272_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fvpsdx hSLMtg"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-271_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-d629" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-kjOQFR ctEqvM pf-262_ pf-hide"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-kjOQFR ctEqvM pf-270_"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-269_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-kjOQFR ctEqvM pf-268_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-nVkyK bhIDty pf-265_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hKumaY imecqU pf-264_">How to Use a Massage Gun For Cellulite?</span></h3><p class="sc-lcepkR datYlM pf-267_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Using a massage gun for cellulite is pretty simple! First of all, make sure that your massage gun has enough of a charge. Most devices are designed with rechargeable batteries. Then, assemble your massage gun and use an attachment that corresponds well with the size of the area where you have cellulite. That usually means choosing a larger attachment, since cellulite is most common over the thighs and buttocks.<br><br>Next, you can start massaging! The best time to massage is when your skin is clean and dry. A lot of people like to use massage guns prior to stretching or after working out. You can make massaging part of your day or night routine.<br><br>Turn the massage gun on a medium setting to start out, and bring it against your skin. Press the device against your skin to create some pressure, and begin moving it over the area where you have cellulite, moving it upwards and downwards in order to promote some lymphatic drainage.<br><br>If the pressure setting you chose feels very mild, you can always increase the pressure. If it’s too intense or painful, turn it down.<br><br>That said, we’d also like to present an alternative: <a href="https://evertoneskin.com/products/body-gua-sha-tool" target="_self">Gua sha for cellulite</a>. Gua sha is a body-scraping massage technique championed by Traditional Chinese Medicine. On the body, a gua sha stone makes it possible to achieve a deeper massage that helps to break down dimple-causing connective bands and encourage lymphatic drainage with minimal strain and without the risks that come from using a massage gun. As a bonus, it’s also more affordable and it’s easy to combine with cellulite-busting topical treatments.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-2d3a" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-ihINtW bFPXVO pf-288_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fvpsdx hSLMtg"><div class="sc-cTAqQK cFxQA-d pf-287_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-to-section="pf-2d3a" data-offset="{&quot;all&qu